description.narrative:
The Quality educators For All overall goal is to assist public authorities provide quality education. This will be done by ensuringthat the roots of the education system remains in the society it serves and by creating the viable partnerships necessary to nurture the system. This object will be realised though the achievement of these specific aims:
# To facilitate access to high quality teachers# education in cooperation with the member organizations of EI and the partner organizations of Oxfam-Novib and in agreement with the national and/or local authorities;
# To design, in cooperation with the EI Higher Education network, the EI Research Institute and a higher education institution specializing in teachers# education, a competency profile for educators, directed in the first instance at primary education, but with possibilities for expansion and adaptation to other levels of education, and based on a modern high quality teacher training curriculum that integrates the teaching of basic literacy andnumeracy with schooling in life and ITskills, gender equality, active citizenship, HIV-Aids prevention, anti-violence, etc;
# To develop and provide, in the first instance, initial and in-service teacher education programmes for unqualified and/or non-formal teachers already in service, to enable them to acquire and improve their professional knowledge and skills. The programme should entail initial intensive courses of from six months to one year#s duration at a minimum, which, when completed successfully, should be followed by further supervised on-the-job training and, finally, certification.  The training should also be open to certified (ex-)teachers who wish, on a voluntary basis, to improve their professional skills;
# To contribute to the development of new high quality models of teacher training which will help to provide the required number of trained teachers to achieve the MDGs;
To develop and provide education programmes #building bridges# between the schools and the wider community, by engaging adults from various backgrounds in the role of educators in the broadest sense of the word. Mothers, youth workers, community volunteers/leaders, and particularly bilingual/indigenous people, communityleaders and elders # should be encouraged tobecome involved in the process of education and particularly of educating educators.
For this period , the project will focus to give sustainability to the project of #Each child need a good teacher# with objective bellow :
Objective General :
 To contribute to the improvement of the quality of education in the area of Ségou through the training of the teachers in 2018.
 Specific objectives:
To reinforce the partnership around the project to ensure the sustainability .
To ensurethe following continues training teachers and the pupils learning in the community schools and   - the Instituts of teachers trainings IFM  area of Ségou;
To diffuse the reference frame of validation of the innovations through the empowerment of the capacities ofthe trainers of the AE/CAP and IFM of the area of Ségou.
 To ensure the follow-up of the assets of the formation continues on the practices of class and the school
To acquire the standardization of the statute of the teachers by the continuation of the integrationof teachers ECOM in the public office of the State or the communities;
